        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Feishu card action mention gating",
        "body": "Fixes #85450.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Mark Feishu synthetic group card-action callbacks with bot mention metadata when `botOpenId` is known.\n- Keep p2p card callbacks unchanged so direct-message callbacks do not gain synthetic mentions.\n- Add regression coverage for both the group mention metadata and the p2p no-mention behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Feishu structured card button callbacks in `requireMention: true` group chats were synthesized as group text messages without bot mention metadata, so the existing group activation gate could treat the callback as not addressing the bot and drop it. After this patch, synthetic group card callbacks include a bot mention entry when `botOpenId` is available, while p2p callbacks still omit synthetic mentions.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/googlerest/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-src`, branch `codex/fix-85450-feishu-card-mention`, commit `2482f7f442 Fix Feishu card action mention gating`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/bot.card-action.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/policy.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output copied from the local OpenClaw checkout:\n\n```text\nRUN  v4.1.6 /Users/googlerest/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-src\n\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\n     Tests  102 passed (102)\n  Start at  02:24:43\n  Duration  3.34s (transform 1.01s, setup 33ms, import 2.34s, tests 843ms, environment 0ms)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The Feishu card-action regression now asserts that a synthetic group callback has `message.chat_type === \"group\"` and includes `mentions: [{ key: \"mention_bot\", id: { open_id: \"ou_bot\" }, name: \"bot\" }]`. The same suite also asserts that p2p card callbacks keep `message.mentions` undefined. The broader Feishu bot and policy regression files passed with the same patch. `git diff --check` completed with no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a live Feishu group chat card click because this local environment does not have live Feishu credentials.\n",
